### Feature 1: Order History & Invoice Generation

**Why**: Customers expect a full receipt/invoice for every completed repair. Currently the profile shows orders but there's no downloadable receipt, no price breakdown, and the `Quote` model in Prisma is unused.

#### Backend Changes

##### [MODIFY] [order.service.ts](file:///d:/Work/App/backend/src/order/order.service.ts)
- Add `generateInvoice(orderId: number)` method that fetches the order with relations (device, serviceCategory, user, technician, quote, feedback) and returns a structured invoice JSON with: order ID, customer name, technician name, device details, service performed, price breakdown (parts + labor + tax), scheduled date, completion date, and warranty period.

##### [NEW] `backend/src/order/invoice.controller.ts`
- `GET /orders/:id/invoice` — Returns the invoice JSON
- `GET /orders/:id/invoice/pdf` — Returns a server-rendered PDF invoice using `pdfkit` (lightweight, zero-headless-browser dependency)

##### [MODIFY] [schema.prisma](file:///d:/Work/App/backend/prisma/schema.prisma)
- Add `completedAt DateTime?` field to Order model
- Add `partsUsed String?` and `laborNotes String?` fields to Order for technicians to fill during repair

#### Frontend Changes

##### [NEW] `mobile-service/src/app/order/order-history/order-history.ts`
- Dedicated order history page with search/filter (by status, date range)
- Each completed order shows an expandable card with full details + "Download Invoice" button
- Route: `/order/history`

##### [MODIFY] [profile.ts](file:///d:/Work/App/mobile-service/src/app/components/profile/profile.ts)
- Replace inline order list with a "View All Orders" button linking to `/order/history`
- Show only the most recent 3 orders in the profile summary

