### Feature 6: AI Diagnostic Pre-Check

**Why**: Trendy apps in 2026 use AI to triage issues before dispatch. This reduces wrong-diagnosis rates, helps technicians prepare the right parts, and makes the user experience feel cutting-edge.

#### Frontend Changes (No Backend AI Required — Client-Side Decision Tree)

##### [NEW] `mobile-service/src/app/order/diagnostic/diagnostic.ts`
- Interactive step-by-step questionnaire:
  1. "What's wrong?" → Select symptoms (cracked screen, won't charge, slow, overheating, water damage, camera blur, etc.)
  2. "When did it start?" → Timeline selector
  3. "Have you tried?" → Checklist of common fixes (restart, safe mode, etc.)
  4. "Photos" → Upload up to 3 photos of the damage (stored as base64 or uploaded to backend)
- AI-style summary: "Based on your symptoms, this appears to be a **charging port corrosion** issue. Estimated repair time: 40 mins. Estimated cost: ₹850–₹1,200."
- "Book Repair" CTA that pre-fills the create-order form with the diagnosed service category
- Route: `/order/diagnostic`

##### [MODIFY] [device-select.ts](file:///d:/Work/App/mobile-service/src/app/order/device-select/device-select.ts)
- Add a prominent "🔍 Diagnose My Device" card alongside the existing device category cards

##### [MODIFY] [create-order.ts](file:///d:/Work/App/mobile-service/src/app/order/create-order/create-order.ts)
- Accept pre-filled service category and notes from the diagnostic flow via query params or localStorage

#### Backend Changes

##### [MODIFY] [schema.prisma](file:///d:/Work/App/backend/prisma/schema.prisma)
- Add `diagnosticNotes String?` and `diagnosticPhotos String[]` to Order model

##### [MODIFY] [order.service.ts](file:///d:/Work/App/backend/src/order/order.service.ts)
- Accept and persist diagnostic data when creating an order

